1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:13,133
Are you leaving or not?

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,333
Okay, we're leaving.

3
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,300
She's going away.
Sorry, Danilo.

4
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:17,233
I couldn't catch her.

5
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,500
She took a taxi.

6
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:22,100
Mommy, promise. I'm okay.
I'm not sick.

7
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:24,100
I'm the only one you've got,
Mookie.

8
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:26,067
We can get through this.

9
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:28,700
I want to know the real results,
Zayn.

10
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:30,333
Then I'll go
and get them for you.

11
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,133
Mookie, I've found
your test results!

12
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,200
You're normal.

13
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:35,633
You're not sick, Mookie.

14
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:37,800
Lucky you to have
that twin bananas.

15
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,233
But just give them away.

16
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:40,400
No!

17
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,133
I won't give my twins away!

18
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,033
How's Mookie?

19
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,833
I believe that's none
of your business, Emma

20
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,967
Why did you lie to me, Mommy?

21
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,800
Are you Maria Angela?

22
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:52,533
What's trickery is it this time?

23
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:55,033
What the hell
are you doing in my house, Jade?

24
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:56,700
Olive!

25
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:41,067
You have a twin, Mommy?

26
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,567
Is that how much you hate me

27
00:01:47,633 --> 00:01:50,900
that you didn't even
mention me to my niece?

28
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,933
Flor, bring Mookie inside.

29
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,533
- I'll just talk to her.
- Okay.

30
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,567
Okay, Ma'am.

31
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:58,767
- Let's go.
- Olive!

32
00:01:58,833 --> 00:01:59,467
Hey!

33
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,300
Bye, my niece!

34
00:02:01,367 --> 00:02:03,233
Who told you to come here?

35
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:04,367
Hey!

36
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:06,833
You're hurting me, Olive. Stop.
I'm coming with you.

37
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:07,833
Hurry up!

38
00:02:14,233 --> 00:02:16,200
Ouch! Olive, stop!

39
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:32,900
Don't you want
to play anymore?

40
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:34,667
What a waste of your luck.

41
00:02:34,733 --> 00:02:35,800
She's right.

42
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,300
I'm already not in the mood.

43
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:40,867
It's Isko's fault.

44
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:44,767
Why did he have
to sell twin bananas?

45
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:45,567
That's why...

46
00:02:47,733 --> 00:02:50,867
it reminded me of Elsa and Eva.

47
00:02:50,933 --> 00:02:52,433
I wonder how they're doing.

48
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:58,033
I'm sure they're doing well.

49
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:02,867
They're happy, they get along,
and love each other.

50
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:03,700
Right.

51
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,767
Oh my, Olive!
What are you doing?

52
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,033
Why are you in a hurry?

53
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:17,700
So that's Maria Angela.

54
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:19,300
She's beautiful.

55
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:21,100
Why is she in crutches?

56
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,900
What happened to her?

57
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:25,900
And why was she so mad at you?
She said you were a liar.

58
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,433
What did you do?

59
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:31,067
You have no right
coming to my house.

60
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:35,933
Didn't I tell you never
to show up to me ever!

61
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:40,600
Come on, Olive. Relax.

62
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:41,933
It's been 20 years
since we last saw each other.

63
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,867
Didn't you miss me?

64
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:47,067
You're dead to me.

65
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:48,467
Ouch!

66
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:51,600
Olive, that's too harsh.

67
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:53,367
Dead, really?

68
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:55,833
You left me, Jade.

69
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:59,700
I'd been helping you
since we were kids.

70
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:03,100
I covered up all your mischiefs.

71
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:04,467
Wait, wait.

72
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:06,967
Are you keeping scores?

73
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:08,600
Shut up!

74
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:11,400
I did everything to help you,

75
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:14,833
especially when you got addicted
to drugs when our parents died.

76
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,233
I never left you.

77
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:29,433
Olive, please help me.
I want to stop.

78
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:32,500
Please help me.
I want to be treated.

79
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:35,200
Please bring me
to a rehabilitation facility.

80
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:36,633
Please, Olive. Bring me...

81
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:37,733
No!

82
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:40,633
No!

83
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,633
Olive, please help me.

84
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:43,900
You'll stay here.

85
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:44,967
Please...

86
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:48,067
I will take care of you.

87
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:50,133
I'll take care of you, Jade.

88
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,767
I'll help you.

89
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:55,867
I'll help you.

90
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:05,467
But what did you do in return?

91
00:05:05,533 --> 00:05:07,900
You left me!

92
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:09,867
I didn't leave you!

93
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:12,433
I escaped from you!

94
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:17,133
I became more addicted
because of you!

95
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,567
Olive, I'm begging you!

96
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:34,633
I don't want this anymore!

97
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:38,567
I don't want this anymore!
I want to get treated!

98
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,467
I don't want this anymore!
I'm begging you!

99
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:50,367
Get me out of here, Olive!

100
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:53,200
Olive!

101
00:05:53,267 --> 00:05:55,267
I needed to leave you.

102
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:57,833
Because you were toxic.

103
00:05:59,167 --> 00:06:01,067
Instead of treating me...

104
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:05,133
you made my addiction worse!

105
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,567
Jade.

106
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:21,667
I promise you...

107
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:26,567
I will take care of you forever.

108
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:28,300
I love you so much...

109
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:31,767
my dear sister.

110
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,667
It was your decision to become
a druggie in the first place.

111
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:39,133
I just helped you.

112
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,100
I enabled you.

113
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,867
I enabled you
because I love you.

114
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:47,933
You made me depend on you.

115
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:52,367
You didn't love me.
You controlled my life!

116
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:54,033
Me!

117
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:57,133
I'm the one who truly loves you,
Olive!

118
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:01,833
Because even if I left you,
I couldn't cut ties with you!

119
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:06,100
I tried several times
to reach out to you.

120
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:08,967
I'm worried about you, Olive!

121
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:12,433
And even if I shouldn't
ask for your forgiveness,

122
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:15,733
I still did so many times
because I left you!

123
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:20,633
What you did is
unforgivable.

124
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,467
No, Olive. You're wrong.

125
00:07:25,533 --> 00:07:27,500
What you did...

126
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:32,000
is what's unforgivable.

127
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:36,433
But I still choose
to forgive you...

128
00:07:37,767 --> 00:07:39,900
even if you're not
asking for it.

129
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:43,233
And that...

130
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:47,567
that's what true love is.

131
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,733
Oh!

132
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,333
Oh, Mookie!

133
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:57,500
This kid. Why did you go out?

134
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:59,233
Where are you going?

135
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:02,167
Flor, I'm waiting for Mommy.

136
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,933
Careful.

137
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,467
She has a lot to explain.

138
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:11,300
I can't understand.

139
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,133
She lied to me
about my sickness.

140
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,433
And now,

141
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:17,000
now I've found out
she has a twin.

142
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:20,733
What else do I have
to know about her?

143
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,967
What else is she hiding from me?

144
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,367
Flor, what's that?

145
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:36,167
I have no idea.

146
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:38,833
- Can you get it for me?
- Okay. I will.

147
00:08:41,333 --> 00:08:42,467
Thank you, Flor.

148
00:08:42,533 --> 00:08:43,533
There.

149
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,900
What's this?

150
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:05,467
It is true that there
are two types of canixidol.

151
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:10,367
One for humans
and one for animals.

152
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:15,633
The one my mom administer
on me...

153
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,933
is for animals.

154
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,067
My God!

155
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:25,033
Why would Ma'am Olive
do that to you?

156
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,133
I don't know.

157
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:33,833
Why do people...

158
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,767
administer...

159
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:40,533
animal medicines on humans?

160
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,400
What does it say?

161
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:51,767
It says some use it
for drug addiction.

162
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:57,500
And some use it to make
other people sick.

163
00:09:57,567 --> 00:10:00,667
So your suspicion is right?

164
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:01,733
But why?

165
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:05,000
Why is Ma'am Olive
making you sick?

166
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:08,800
Munchausen Syndrome by Proxy?

167
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:11,367
What's that? What's Munchau?

168
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,267
Its a psychological disorder...

169
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,567
who often sees in mothers,
then...

170
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:20,400
and they're making
their children sick.

171
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:24,433
My God.

172
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:29,100
Just like what my mom
does to me.

173
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,367
Mookie...

174
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:43,733
There's no reason for us
to see each other.

175
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,933
I really had no plan
to show up to you, Olive.

176
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:49,267
But I have to.

177
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:53,033
I don't have money anymore.

178
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:56,567
I only want to get my share
in the ancestral house.

179
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,133
What happened
to your inheritance?

180
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,967
Did you squander it?

181
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,200
When I migrated to Japan...

182
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:07,600
I couldn't manage
my money properly.

183
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,600
It's your karma.

184
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:13,667
You wouldn't have suffered
if you hadn't left.

185
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:17,100
Or I would have been long dead
because of my addiction.

186
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:23,467
I have no regrets, Olive.

187
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,167
I just want to start again,
so...

188
00:11:27,233 --> 00:11:28,467
No.

189
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:31,633
I won't sell
the ancestral house.

190
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,500
Fine, if that's your decision.

191
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,600
So, if that's the case, then...

192
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,600
then I will live in your house.

193
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:44,533
That would be okay so I can
spend time with Maria Angela.

194
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,600
And that's what you want, right?

195
00:11:48,067 --> 00:11:51,067
That will be together forever.

196
00:11:51,133 --> 00:11:53,333
And I can also help you
with the pharmacy.

197
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,700
What?

198
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:56,200
No!

199
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:58,667
What do we do now?

200
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:03,100
I have nowhere else
to stay here in the Philippines.

201
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:06,467
I can't go back to Japan without
money because...

202
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:10,633
I owe a lot of people money
there.

203
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,467
Fine, fine.

204
00:12:15,633 --> 00:12:20,200
I will sell the ancestral house
and give your share,

205
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:21,800
but on one condition.

206
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:26,100
Don't ever come to my house.

207
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:29,000
Don't ever show up
to me and my child

208
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:31,900
while I'm looking for a buyer.

209
00:12:31,967 --> 00:12:33,933
Okay, Olive.

210
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,133
I got it.

211
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:39,100
But...

212
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:44,833
I need an advance money.

213
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,467
200,000 pesos.

214
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,000
Thank you so much, Olive.

215
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:11,267
Get out of my car.

216
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:14,767
Can't I have a hug?

217
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:18,033
I missed you, Olive.

218
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,233
That's true.

219
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,700
Out!

220
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,500
Mookie, what are we doing here?

221
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:02,500
And why did you tell me
to bring the hammer?

222
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,500
What are you doing? What's that?

223
00:14:08,733 --> 00:14:09,500
Mookie!

224
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:13,033
Mookie, what are you doing?
Please stop!

225
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:17,267
Mookie, stop! Hey!

226
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:18,800
What are you looking for?

227
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:35,933
Bukoy, your phone's ringing.

228
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,033
It seems that
your boss is calling.

229
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:41,267
He just wants to check
if I'm going to work.

230
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:43,267
I'm in night shift today.

231
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:45,300
But I wasn't able
to file a leave.

232
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:47,067
Then go to work.

233
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,533
No, it's okay.

234
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:52,833
He'll find someone to replace me
if I don't answer his call.

235
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:55,100
But you won't make money today.

236
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:58,433
You can't just spend
your time with us.

237
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,833
But what do we do?

238
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,933
I'm the only one who knows what
Kayla's kidnapper looks like.

239
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:09,667
I know what to do.

240
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:12,667
Here's what I'll do,
I still have a paid leave.

241
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:14,267
I'll use tomorrow.

242
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:17,967
So it'll be okay
even if we stay out late.

243
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:22,567
Bukoy, thanks for all you do
for our family.

244
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:24,800
No problem. Anything for Kayla.

245
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,167
Let's go?

246
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,267
Don't waste it!

247
00:15:37,967 --> 00:15:40,600
Mookie, stop!

248
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,600
Oh, no!

249
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,067
Darn it!

250
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:50,733
Where is...

251
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,500
Yes, Ma'am.

252
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:53,767
- Come on.
- Oh, Olive!

253
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:54,500
Hey!

254
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:55,967
Bye, my niece!

255
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,500
Did Mookie see it?

256
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,667
Mookie, stop!

257
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:13,667
Mookie, don't...

258
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:14,467
Mookie, stop.

259
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:16,000
Mookie! Come on!

260
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:19,800
You're so stubborn!

261
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:21,400
Give that to me, Flor.

262
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:22,600
Don't do it.

263
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:26,867
Mookie, that's enough!

264
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:28,533
Mookie, stop!

265
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,433
What's going on here?
Mookie?

266
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:34,733
Mookie, what's the matter here?

267
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,433
Mookie, what are you doing?

268
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,533
Getting rid of the things
that make me sick.

269
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:42,833
I already know the truth, Mommy.

270
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:46,033
You're faking my test results!

271
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,533
Why would I fake
my test results?

272
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,767
Mommy, don't deny it.

273
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:53,833
I already know the truth.

274
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:59,033
You're giving me
canixidol for animals!

275
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,600
Mookie,
what are you talking about?

276
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:04,567
Mommy, stop denying it, please!

277
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:07,200
I already know what
you're doing to me!

278
00:17:08,167 --> 00:17:11,667
I already know the truth, Mommy.
I've seen it on the internet.

279
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:17,100
You are making me sick!

280
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,600
Mommy, I don't understand
why you're doing this to me.

281
00:17:38,667 --> 00:17:42,800
Why, Mommy? Why?

282
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:45,100
What did I do to deserve this?

283
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,267
Mookie.

284
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,933
Mookie, please let me explain.

285
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,167
Mommy, what's more to explain?

286
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:55,467
I don't understand
why you're doing this to me!

287
00:17:57,367 --> 00:18:01,000
Because all the people I love
leave me!

288
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:06,867
My mom, my dad,
my twin, your dad!

289
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:09,733
All of them left me!

290
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:12,367
I don't want that
to happen again!

291
00:18:12,433 --> 00:18:14,667
I don't want to lose you.

292
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:16,933
You're really making me sick...

293
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:21,033
so that I won't leave you,
Mommy?

294
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,900
Mookie, please.

295
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:29,633
Don't touch me.

296
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,800
- Don't touch me, Mommy!
- Mookie, please let me explain.

297
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,533
Don't touch me!

298
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:37,833
You know what, Mommy?

299
00:18:39,767 --> 00:18:41,567
I'm not the one sick.

300
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:44,367
You...

301
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,967
It's you! You're mentally sick.

302
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:49,333
That's why you should be
left behind!

303
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,167
Ma'am!

304
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:06,733
I hope we see the woman
in the hotel tomorrow, Emma.

305
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:10,233
I really hope so.

306
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:14,233
The taxi driver isn't sure
if she went inside the hotel.

307
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:16,833
What if she only got off
in that area?

308
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:23,467
Emma, don't be a pessimist.

309
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:26,967
Let's just pray
to see her tomorrow.

310
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:30,467
Do you want to eat that
while walking?

311
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:32,567
Come on. Let's go home.

312
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:40,167
I'm sorry.

313
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:41,200
I'm sorry, Mookie.

314
00:19:41,267 --> 00:19:42,233
I didn't mean to do that.

315
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:43,533
Mookie, I'm sorry.

316
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,000
- Mookie!
- I got this, Mookie.

317
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,533
- Mookie, please! Mookie.
- Here you go.

318
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,833
Mookie, please,
let's talk about this.

319
00:19:54,567 --> 00:19:55,500
Mookie!

320
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:58,033
Mookie, wait!

321
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,667
Mookie!

322
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:02,533
I am asking you! Where are you
going?

323
00:20:02,633 --> 00:20:04,200
I'm going to leave, Mommy.

324
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,500
Leave?

325
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:10,000
You have nowhere else to go.

326
00:20:10,067 --> 00:20:11,933
I'm everything you've got.

327
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,600
No.

328
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:16,700
I'll go to Mommy Emma.
She'll take care of me.

329
00:20:16,767 --> 00:20:19,000
She won't do the things
you did to me.

330
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:21,133
She will never make me sick.

331
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:24,033
- You have no choice...
- Ma'am! Ma'am! Ma'am!

332
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:25,033
Ma'am, please stop. Ma'am.

333
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:27,000
Please stop.
You're hurting Mookie.

334
00:20:27,067 --> 00:20:29,267
Please have mercy on Mookie,
Ma'am.

335
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,867
Please have mercy.

336
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,500
Ma'am! Ma'am!

337
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,367
Ma'am!

338
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:38,833
- Ma'am!
- Mommy!

339
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,300
Mommy, are you okay?

340
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:42,300
Ma'am! Ma'am! Please get up.

341
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:45,533
Mookie, why are you doing
this to me?

342
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:49,533
I took care of you all my life!

343
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:50,900
Took care?

344
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,567
Do you want to be
paralyzed forever?

345
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:58,767
I don't want to, Mommy.

346
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,500
You're infection
is getting worse.

347
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:02,900
We need to consult
another doctor.

348
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,900
What for? I'm a doctor.

349
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:09,200
That's one of the complications
of a spinal injury.

350
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:13,367
In your case, you're paralyzed
and your mobility is limited.

351
00:21:13,433 --> 00:21:17,500
Your leg will get amputated
if it gets worse.

352
00:21:19,067 --> 00:21:20,633
You're getting worse.

353
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:23,200
You might not be able
to walk again.

354
00:21:23,267 --> 00:21:27,133
You will never change no matter
what I do to you.

355
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:31,033
So your horn must be cut off.

356
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:35,300
We'll get through this, Dear.

357
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:36,833
I won't leave you.

358
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:45,267
I've found your test results.

359
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:47,667
You're normal!
You're not sick, Mookie!

360
00:21:47,733 --> 00:21:50,767
You didn't take care of me,
Mommy.

361
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:53,833
You made me dependent on you.

362
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:54,867
No!

363
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:59,167
No! No!

364
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:02,000
Don't leave me! Mookie, please!

365
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:05,500
Catch her!

366
00:22:14,367 --> 00:22:15,100
Oh!

367
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,200
Hey! Hey!

368
00:22:16,267 --> 00:22:18,000
- Hey, wait! Snatcher!
- Hey, my cell phone!

369
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:19,100
Cell phone!

370
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:21,133
It's unbecoming of a woman!

371
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,000
Bring her to the barangay hall!

372
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:25,033
Bring her
to the barangay office!

373
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:27,400
- Gosh!
- Unbelievable!

374
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:28,733
Miss?

375
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,900
Here's your cell phone.

376
00:22:29,967 --> 00:22:32,467
Thank you so much.

377
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:36,333
Thank you so much.
Thank you. Thank you.

378
00:22:41,567 --> 00:22:43,800
Mookie! Mookie, I'm sorry.

379
00:22:43,867 --> 00:22:44,800
- Flor.
- I can't let you

380
00:22:44,867 --> 00:22:45,833
- go out.
- Mookie!

381
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:48,033
You know what your mom
will do to me.

382
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,833
Flor, let me go, please.

383
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:53,433
You know what will mom to do me
if she catches me right?

384
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,200
Flor, don't let Mookie leave!

385
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:57,033
- Mookie, please.
- Flor, please.

386
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:59,767
Stop Mookie! She mustn't leave!

387
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:02,133
- Hit me! Hurt me!
- Flor!

388
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,500
- Don't let Mookie get away.
- Hurry! Hurt me!

389
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:04,567
Hit me! Hard!

390
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:07,567
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

391
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:09,467
Stop her!

392
00:23:09,533 --> 00:23:10,600
Mookie!

393
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:14,033
- Flor! Stop her!
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

394
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:15,333
- Ma'am!
- Ouch!

395
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,367
What's happening to you?

396
00:23:16,433 --> 00:23:17,533
It hurts!

397
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,533
- Oh, Ma'am!
- Mookie!

398
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:29,367
Mommy, I will never leave you.

399
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:30,867
I promise.

400
00:23:30,933 --> 00:23:31,967
Liar!

401
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:34,267
I've seen the woman.
She's coming out of the hotel.

402
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,000
She's leaving.

403
00:23:35,067 --> 00:23:36,833
Okay. We're almost there, Bukoy.

404
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:42,200
Now, I can be sure
that you will never leave me.

405
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:44,700
You will be like a living doll.

406
00:23:44,767 --> 00:23:46,867
- Emma! Please help Mookie!
- Flor.

407
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:49,433
Ma'am Olive locked her up
and chained her.

408
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:50,233
Why?

409
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:53,067
Mookie found out she's not sick.

410
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,300
Ma'am Olive has made
everything up.

411
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,633
Go ahead. Go to Mookie.

412
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:57,667
I'll follow you.

413
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:58,867
I will go
to the barangay hall first.

414
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,000
I will report her
to the barangay chairman.

415
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:01,367
Drink it!

416
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:03,100
Stop resisting, Mookie!

417
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:06,700
Don't spit it out! Drink it!
